\f0\b\fs24 \cf0 CopperExport for iPhoto\
Version [[version]]\

\f1\b0 [[date]].\
\
CopperExport for iPhoto is a plugin for iPhoto 4 and 5 which allows you to export pictures directly into a Coppermine gallery (http://coppermine.sf.net/).\
\

\f0\b As of version 0.4.0, CopperExport is built as a universal binary. 
\f1\b0  I don't have an Intel-based Mac to test, but if you do, please let me know if it works correctly!\
\
I would love to hear from you if you find it useful, or if you find something that does not work properly, or if you have any other comments or suggestions. See the email address at the bottom of this document.\
\
See the ChangeLog file for a detailed list of changes.\
\

\f0\b \ul System Requirements
\f1\b0 \
\ulnone \
CopperExport for iPhoto requires Mac OS X 10.3 or later and iPhoto 4.x or 5.x.  iPhoto 2.x and iPhoto 6 
\f2\i may
\f1\i0  work, but has not been tested.  Versions of Mac OS X prior to 10.3 will certainly not work.\
\
It has been tested with Coppermine 1.3.2, 1.3.3 and 1.4.3. Older versions may work, but have not been tested. See the notes below on optional (but recommended) server-side configuration.\
\

\f0\b \ul Installation
\f1\b0 \
\ulnone \
1. Double click on the CopperExport.pkg package file.\
2. Follow the instructions of the installer.\
3. Apply the server-side configuration (see below) to be able to set photo titles, descriptions and keywords.\
\
