\f0\b \cf0 \ul \ulc0 Server-side configuration\

\f3\i \ulnone \
Please note: 
\f2\b0 if you had installed 
\f4\i0 xp_publish.php
\f2\i  from CopperExport 0.1, please replace it with the new version to support setting the description when creating a new album.\

\f3\b \cf2 IMPORTANT: 
\f2\b0 The version of xp_publish.php distributed with CopperExport 0.2 and prior contained a security vulnerability. Please update to the new version!
\f1\i0 \cf0 \

\f0\b \

\f1\b0 CopperExport uses the existing "Windows XP export wizard" interface in Coppermine. Unfortunately, in the default distribution of Coppermine, this interface does not accept additional information like the title, description and keywords for a picture, or the description for new albums. If you have access to your Coppermine installation directory, you can make some small changes to enable this functionality.\
\

\f2\i If you cannot do not have the possibility of making these changes, you can still upload files, but the caption, description and keywords will not be applied, or the description for new albums.\

\f1\i0 \
In the cpg-patches folder, you can find the following files:\
\
\pard\tx720\tx1440\tx2160\tx2880\tx3600\tx4320\tx5040\tx5760\tx6480\tx7200\tx7920\tx8640\ql\qnatural

\f4 \cf0 xp_publish.php.cpgXYZ
\f1 : this is the file from release X.Y.Z of Coppermine, already with the necessary modifications. Simply replace the existing 
\f4 xp_publish.php
\f1  file in your Coppermine installation directory with the corresponding file.\
\

\f4 xp_publish.php.cpgXYZ.patch
\f1 : is a patch file containing the necessary changes. Copy the appropriate file to your Coppermine installation directory, log into the Coppermine server and run the following commands:\
\

\f4 cd /your/coppermine/directory\
patch -p0 < xp_publish.php.cpgXYZ.patch
\f1 \
\
The result should be the same as if you had copied 
\f4 xp_publish.php.cpgXYZ
\f1 .\
In both cases, make sure you make a copy of the original 
\f4 xp_publish.php
\f1  file before making any changes, so you can revert to it if anything goes wrong.\
\
The changes to 
\f4 xp_publish.php
\f1  do not affect the capability of uploading things from Windows XP.
